trans-unit.source: Move data to and from Oracle | Azure Data Factory
trans-unit.target: Move data to and from Oracle | Azure Data Factory

trans-unit.source: Learn how to move data to/from Oracle database that is on-premises using Azure Data Factory.
trans-unit.target: Learn how to move data to/from Oracle database that is on-premises using Azure Data Factory.

trans-unit.source: Move data to on-premises Oracle using Azure Data Factory
trans-unit.target: Move data to on-premises Oracle using Azure Data Factory

trans-unit.source: This article outlines how you can use data factory copy activity to move data from Oracle to another data store.
trans-unit.target: This article outlines how you can use data factory copy activity to move data from Oracle to another data store.

trans-unit.source: This article builds on the [data movement activities](data-factory-data-movement-activities.md) article which presents a general overview of data movement with copy activity and supported data store combinations.
trans-unit.target: This article builds on the [data movement activities](data-factory-data-movement-activities.md) article which presents a general overview of data movement with copy activity and supported data store combinations.

trans-unit.source: Sample: Copy data from Oracle to Azure Blob
trans-unit.target: Sample: Copy data from Oracle to Azure Blob

trans-unit.source: A [pipeline](data-factory-create-pipelines.md) with Copy activity that uses [OracleSource](data-factory-onprem-oracle-connector.md#oracle-copy-activity-type-properties) as source and [BlobSink](data-factory-azure-blob-connector.md#azure-blob-copy-activity-type-properties) as sink.
trans-unit.target: A [pipeline](data-factory-create-pipelines.md) with Copy activity that uses [OracleSource](data-factory-onprem-oracle-connector.md#oracle-copy-activity-type-properties) as source and [BlobSink](data-factory-azure-blob-connector.md#azure-blob-copy-activity-type-properties) as sink.

trans-unit.source: The sample copies data from a table in an on-premises Oracle database to a blob every hour.
trans-unit.target: The sample copies data from a table in an on-premises Oracle database to a blob every hour.

trans-unit.source: For more information on various properties used in the sample below please refer to documentation on different properties in the sections following the samples.
trans-unit.target: For more information on various properties used in the sample below please refer to documentation on different properties in the sections following the samples.

trans-unit.source: The sample assumes you have created a table “MyTable” in Oracle and it contains a column called “timestampcolumn” for time series data.
trans-unit.target: The sample assumes you have created a table “MyTable” in Oracle and it contains a column called “timestampcolumn” for time series data.

trans-unit.source: Setting “external”: ”true” and specifying externalData policy tells data factory that this is a table that is external to the data factory and not produced by an activity in the data factory.
trans-unit.target: Setting “external”: ”true” and specifying externalData policy tells data factory that this is a table that is external to the data factory and not produced by an activity in the data factory.

trans-unit.source: Data is written to a new blob every hour (frequency: hour, interval: 1).
trans-unit.target: Data is written to a new blob every hour (frequency: hour, interval: 1).

trans-unit.source: The folder path and file name for the blob are dynamically evaluated based on the start time of the slice that is being processed.
trans-unit.target: The folder path and file name for the blob are dynamically evaluated based on the start time of the slice that is being processed.

trans-unit.source: The folder path uses year, month, day, and hours parts of the start time.
trans-unit.target: The folder path uses year, month, day, and hours parts of the start time.

trans-unit.source: The pipeline contains a Copy Activity that is configured to use the above input and output datasets and is scheduled to run every hour.
trans-unit.target: The pipeline contains a Copy Activity that is configured to use the above input and output datasets and is scheduled to run every hour.

trans-unit.source: In the pipeline JSON definition, the **source** type is set to **RelationalSource** and **sink** type is set to **BlobSink**.
trans-unit.target: In the pipeline JSON definition, the **source** type is set to **RelationalSource** and **sink** type is set to **BlobSink**.

trans-unit.source: The SQL query specified with **oracleReaderQuery** property selects the data in the past hour to copy.
trans-unit.target: The SQL query specified with **oracleReaderQuery** property selects the data in the past hour to copy.
